{"TopicId":203511,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"Kerbals with colored Hair","CreatedByName":"Sky Kerman","CreatedById":208997,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-01T11:54:18Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sky Kerman","CreatedById":208997,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-01T11:54:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the game should have Kerbals with like red hair or blue or something. To mix it up a little bit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jimmymcgoochie","CreatedById":199902,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-01T12:39:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgreed- though judging by the most recent dev diary, this might already be happening in KSP2. In the meantime, Texture Replacer lets\u00A0you customise your Kerbals in KSP with different hair styles and colours, facial hair and skin tones- much better than generic clones that all look identical.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dientus","CreatedById":209823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-01T17:02:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/199902-jimmymcgoochie/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022199902\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/199902-jimmymcgoochie/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@jimmymcgoochie\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0 describes sums up the way I took the presentation as well. Why not add the hair to it then if it hasn\u0027t been added yet? I see blue and grey hair being a thing now. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;p\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/971609041_P.png\u0022 title=\u0022;p\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"greenville","CreatedById":225289,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-04T20:53:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u002